title: Fixed the way Ramda is required
body:
This commit comes from my need to use Maybe only as I do not need the rest. Thus,
I do `require('ramda-fantasy/src/Maybe')`. But the problem with the old way of doing require in `ramda-fantasy` is that tree shaking can not be performed.
Although only three functions are used in this module from `ramda`, the whole library (`ramda`) is included in my build through `ramda-fantasy`.

I use rollup in order to build my code as it can perform tree shaking. Thus, the features that are not required in my code are not included in build. However, dependencies
also need to include the only parts they need.

title: integrate sanctuary-def
body:
See #89

Advantages:
- :white_check_mark: centralized, consistent approach to type checking
- :white_check_mark: currying (without `R.curry`)
- :white_check_mark: no "abstract bases classes"; no inheritance
- :white_check_mark: no unreliable `instanceof` checks (if #81 is accepted)
- :white_check_mark: increased implementation overlap with Sanctuary
- :white_check_mark: straightforward [Transcribe](https://github.com/plaid/transcribe) integration if desired

Disadvantages:
- :x: additional dependency

This pull request currently only updates **src/Either.js**, to provide something concrete to discuss. If the rest of the team is on board I'll update the other files similarly.
